νόμοισιν αὐ. πόλιν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 191, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.7.2\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>exalt by one's deeds, glorify,</b> πόλιν, πάτραν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 5.4, “P.” 8.38, compare “IG” 22.834, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>exalt by praise, extol,</b> ἐπαινεῖν καὶ αὔξειν τινά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Lysis” 206a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σέ γε.. καὶ τροφὸν καὶ ματέρ᾽ αὔξειν <b>honour</b> thee <b>as</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1092 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of an orator, <b>amplify, exaggerate,</b> αὔξειν καὶ μειοῦν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1403a17. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with an <i>adjective</i>, τρέφειν καὶ αὐ. τινὰ μέγαν <b>bring up</b> to manhood, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 565c; μείζω πόλιν αὐ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 572 (Lyric poetry); τὸν ὄγκον.. ἄπειρον αὐξήσει 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 591d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> αὔξειν ἔμπυρα <b>to sacrifice,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).62\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; compare ἀέξω. <br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> in Logic, ={καταπυκνόω} (which see), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Posteriora” 79a30, +others\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; but ὁ αὐξόμενος λόγος, name of a <b>fallacy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Theseus” 23, 2.559b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>grow, increase,</b> in size, number, strength, power, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 493, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 8.93, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 61.5, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; αὐ. ἐς πλῆθος, ἐς ὕψος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.58, 2.14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a child, <b>grow up,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.92\">Refs</a>].; ἐν γὰρ τοῖς πόνοισιν αὔξεται, of Theseus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 323\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ηὐξανόμην ἀκούων I <b>grew taller</b> as I heard, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 638 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the wind, <b>rise,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.188; ηὔξηται ἡ πόλις ὥστ᾽ εἶναι τελέα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 371e. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with an <i>adjective</i>, αὔξεσθαι μέγας <b>wax</b> great, <b>grow</b> up, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 183; αὐ. μείζων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 338, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 681a; αὐ. ἐλλόγιμος [prev. author] “Prt.” 327c; μέγας ἐκ μικροῦ.. ηὔξηται 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.21. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> later, <i>active</i> <i>intransitive</i>, like <i>passive</i>, ἡ σελήνη αὐξάνει[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Posteriora” 78b6, compare “HA” 620a21, Aristeas 208, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 4.64, NT.Col.2.19, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator Chr. 4.128, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 48.52, etc. \">NT+4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> of Verbs, <b>take the augment,</b> both <i>active</i> and <i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus “Epim.” 280\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; αὔξουσα (i.e. συλλαβή), ἡ, <b>augment,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage] (Cf. ἀέξω.) \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G0837","accentedUnicode":"αὐξάνω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0838","matchingForm":"αὔξησις","stepTransliteration":"auxēsis","gloss":"growth","_zh_tw_Gloss":"增長力, 增長","_es_Gloss":"crecimiento","_zh_Gloss":"增长力, 增长"}],"shortDef":"to cause to grow; (intr.) grow, increase","mediumDef":"to cause to grow; (intr.) grow, increase <br />also spelled <greek>αὔξω</greek>, <i>transitive</i> <b>to cause to grow</b> or <b>increase;</b> <i>passive</i> <b>to be increased, enlarged,</b> <ref='Mat.13.32'>Mt. 13:32</ref>; <ref='1Co.3.6'>1Cor. 3:6</ref>, 7; <i>intransitive</i> <b>to increase, grow,</b> <ref='Mat.6.28'>Mt. 6:28</ref>; <ref='Mrk.4.8'>Mk. 4:8</ref>","stepGloss":"to grow","stepTransliteration":"auxanō","count":23,"_es_Definition":"intrans. crecer ; cultivar, propagar, aumentar ; volverse más importante (JN.3:30); alcanzar el crecimiento total (MAT.13:32); trans. hacer crecer, incrementar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 使之成長, 增加 (範圍, 大小, 狀態, 或質素)<br>2) 成長, 增加","_zh_Definition":"1) 使之成长, 增加 (范围, 大小, 状态, 或质素)<br>2) 成长, 增加","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"tăng trưởng; tăng lên","_zh_tw_Gloss":"長大","_es_Gloss":"crecer","_zh_Gloss":"长大"}]}